			<div class='step grid-30'>
				<h2>1</h2>
				<p>Connect your Twitter account</p>
			</div>
			<div class='form-element grid-70'>
				<p>
				Connecting your Twitter account allows us to make the connection needed to integrate your Twitter feed with your displays. Don’t worry, we can’t see your password, post on your wall, or generally do anything not cool. That being said, if you like the software, we’re always appreciative of a social media shout out <a href='http://twitter.com/boltstudiosokc'>@boltstudiosokc</a>.
				</p>

				<img src='/images/how-does-this-work/1.jpg' />
			</div>
		</div>

		<div class='grid-100 grid-parent'>
			<div class='step grid-30'>
				<h2>2</h2>
				<p>Choose your display</p>
			</div>
			<div class='form-element grid-70 grid-parent'>
				<p>
				If you have a video mixer, Favorite Wall allows you to overlay your feed on top of video. If that sounds cool, but you have no idea what that means, <a href='#' data-target='what-the-heck'>click here</a>.

				<div name='what-the-heck' class='tell-me-more' role='hidden'>
					<i class='icon-remove'></i>
					Mixing two streams of information together is called chroma keying. Using chroma key compositing, your video mixer <a href='http://www.amazon.com/Roland-V-4-4-Channel-Video-Mixer/dp/B0002I6M02/' target='_blank'>(one like this)</a> can remove the green background from your Twitter feed being displayed. Simply show your browser full screen, feed it into your video mixer, and layer it on top of your live video stream.
				</div>
				</p>

				<p>
				You have two options if you’re overlaying the video. You can either continuously loop your latest favorites by choosing <strong>overlay continuous</strong>, or you can have your newest favorite pop on the screen for a few seconds then go away by choosing <strong>overlay new only</strong>.
				</p>


				<p>
				If you don’t have a video mixer, choose full screen. Favorite Wall will take up the entire width of the monitor no matter the size. That’s some skillz with a z type stuff there.
				</p>

				<p>
				The continuous feeds work great for lobbies, hallways and side monitors. The new only screen works really well for interjecting audience interaction during the live event.
				</p>


				<div class='grid-50 display-swapper'>
					<img data-value='fullscreen' src='/images/how-does-this-work/2a.jpg' class='display-image' />
				</div>
				<div class='grid-50 display-swapper'>
					<img data-value='overlay' src='/images/how-does-this-work/2b.jpg' class='display-image' />
