			<div class='form-element grid-70'>
				<p>
				This is the fun part. You can now start favoriting  tweets from any device. Most all Twitter clients will let you follow a search term or a hashtag, and there are several software clients like HootSuite that will let you monitor multiple search terms at once. Maybe you want to see:</p>
				
				<p class='emph'>Who’s talking about your event?<br/>
					What they’re saying about your speaker?<br/>
					Who’s tweeting your hashtag?
				</p>
				<p>
				Plug those search terms in, and anytime you see something you want everyone to see, simply favorite it. Favorite Wall will display up to 8 new tweets every minute.
				</p>

